I can still feel that "Urge-To-Kill" rising... LOLOLOL! My only hope is that someone might find some amusement from my review, and be adequately warned to stay away. After waiting a while, I witnessed the barista picking up an empty grande cup, filling it with Almond Milk.  He then headed to the wall counter and proceeded to PLOP A MEASUREMENT OF MATCHA POWDER IN THE CUP. Barely shaking it, big clumps of matcha floating like disgusting balls of water moss, he places it on the counter. He was perhaps too guilty to give eye contact at my despairing face.  If you ever had the misfortune of trying to drink one of these abominations, you would know it's like drinking Almond Milk with Matcha Boogers. Yuck! Pictures attached.
